text: Al Ahed FC is an acronym. FC stands for "Football Club". is a professional football club that plays in the Lebanese Premier League. They are based in Beirut, the capital city of Lebanon. The club has won 1 AFC Cup title, 8 league titles, 6 Lebanese FA Cup titles, 8 Lebanese Super Cup titles, 5 Lebanese Elite Cup titles, and 1 Lebanese Federation Cup title. In 2019 they became the first club from Lebanon to win the AFC Cup. == Notes == == References == Category:Beirut Category:Lebanese Premier League Category:Organizations based in Lebanon
